description:
With this video you will practice your Spanish listening comprehension skills. You will hear a Spanish conversation between two people. One is late for a dinner invitation. The other person has cooked and has been waiting for her friend. In this conversation you will learn many Spanish phrases that are commonly used by native Spanish speakers. To tell your story, you will learn to use verbs in past, Spanish pretérito -- to talk about what you did -- and in Spanish imperfecto.

This video is the first of many more videos to come in order to help you to understand Spanish more, and comprehend Spanish at the speed and intonation that is natural to native Spanish speakers. Many people who are learning Spanish feel that one of the hardest parts of learning Spanish is to understand native Spanish speakers. The speed, the intonation, and the lack of contact with native Spanish speakers make understanding more difficult. With this video, I am giving you a chance to understand a normal daily conversation at regular speed, while also explaining parts that might help you understand and make sense of the conversation. 

I hope this video will give you the chance to practice more Spanish. This conversation will allow you to practice your listening abilities in Spanish. This video will also give you the chance to listen to a native Spanish speaker as many times as you want by just playing and replaying the video.

description:
In this Spanish comprehension practice you will learn Spanish by listening to me reading reviews my friends have written about places they have visited. We will learn to describe experiences people have at restaurants and bars, you will learn how people give compliments in Spanish, how they complain, and how they talk about experiences with their friends. While listening to so many useful Spanish words and phrases taken from native Spanish speakers in the real world, you will also learn to use the Spanish imperfect, and the Spanish past simple. You will learn some keywords that come in handy when you are conversing with someone about an experience you had at a place you ate, you had a coffee, you had a drink, an ice cream, and so on. In this lesson you will also practice or polish your Spanish comprehension skills.

If you like my videos, and feel you are learning and want to cooperate, please consider making a donation:

You can donate at: https://www.butterflyspanish.com/

Or through PayPal: https://www.paypal.me/ButterflySpanish

Muchas gracias :)

If you want to keep learning handy words, questions, and phrases in Spanish, watch my playlist:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLkjyx6Il3YUYWNS7C1N_qnPS-w-NWEgD9

But before you watch, you need to encourage yourself and need the magic words.
Say: 
I will learn Spanish, voy a aprender español. 
I will learn Spanish, voy a aprender español. 
I will learn Spanish with Ana, voy a aprender español con Ana. 
I will learn Spanish with Ana, voy a aprender español con Ana. 
Ana will hold my hand and take me to México and teach me to speak to people, and not be afraid of speaking the language of love, Spanish. Not French! French whatever… just to show off.

description:
Are you saying "espero que estés bien" or “espero que estás bien”? Learn to use the present subjunctive in everyday Spanish conversation. Learn to express your thoughts, hopes and wishes using the subjunctive. I will teach you many useful, everyday Spanish phrases that require the subjunctive. I will explain to you why you need the subjunctive in phrases that start with the words "I hope that..." (Espero que..."), and I will give you all the information you need to understand the present subjunctive. In only this 20 minute video you will correct one of the most common mistakes Spanish learners make from beginner level to very advanced level. More importantly, I will teach you all this in a very easy way so you will end up loving Spanish grammar.

In this Spanish lesson you will learn kitchen vocabulary, expressions, verbs, names of dishes, spices, and flavors. You will learn important Spanish verbs used in the Mexican kitchen such as "freír", "picar", "cocer", "calentar", "moler", "pelar", and so on. You will learn about classic Mexican flavors like "picante", "picosito", "grasoso", "amargo", "salado", "simple", and so on. You will also learn about dishes like "mole" and how this dish might be related to he verb "moler", "to grind". You will learn about expressions like "le falta" ("it is missing"'), "me salió bueno", and more used in the Mexican cuisine. This lesson will help you to describe a dish, to ask for a recipe, to give a recipe or to execute a dish. You will be given the vocabulary and expressions that are handy when you are in the kitchen cooking, following a recipe or giving your secret recipe to your friends. This Spanish lesson will help you improve your Spanish while focusing in the kitchen. Watch my video and learn Spanish for the kitchen, and learn some culture aspects of the cuisine.

Have a conversation in Spanish at the dinner table! Learn words, phrases, questions, and answers related to dining. Don't say "I wish I knew how to say this and that." Instead, learn to say it. Next time you are at the table just about to eat, you will know how to say in Spanish "pass me the pepper", or the the salt or the hot sauce, "How did you make this?, "Did you like it?", "Was it good?", "Enjoy!", and more. With this lesson, you will learn everyday, useful, practical Spanish.

Watch this lesson and learn some important words while also practicing your comprehension with the sentences I wrote and that I took from conversations I had with my friends, sisters, brothers, and nieces, _sobrinas_ like Dani and her sister Karoli. Enjoy the class and Merry December. _Disfruta este mes de la manera que más te gusta._

Ana of the Julii
